-- France Has No Plans to Review Fracking Ban, Energy Minister Says
-- B y   S t e v e   R h i n d s
-- 2012-07-20T06:48:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-20/france-has-no-plans-to-review-fracking-ban-energy-minister-says.html
The French government currently has
no plans to lift a ban on hydraulic fracturing, known as
fracking, the technique used to extract gas and oil from shale
rock, Environment and Energy Minister Delphine Batho said in an
interview with radio station RMC today.  Batho also said there are no plans for a freeze on gasoline
prices at the moment.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Rhinds at 
 srhinds@bloomberg.net  